line.comment: * Summary:
* Sell or unload ware to contragent of any possible type:
* station, ship docked at, remote ship.
* The script must be used for all ware transfers from this ship.
* This needed to provide signal generating for remote transfers.
* Arguments:
* $WareStruct - WareStruct of ware to unload from cargo bay.
* $Amount - Amount to be unloaded.
* $Target - Station or ship to unload to (optional).
* The main goal of the argument is to specify remote ship to transfer to.
* If target is a station, then additional check of equality with DOCKEDAT
* will be executed. If omitted, then DOCKEDAT will be used.
* $Price - The min price to sell at station or fixed price for remote transfer.
* This parameter is optional. If not specified and target is a station, then
* station price will be used. If not specified and target is a ship, then
* then average price of ware will be used.
* Returns:
* Actual amount of ware sold.
* Begin Constants section v3.02.12
* End of Constants section
